@SavchukRomanLv This commit currently blocks test_forward_ip_packet_with_0xffff_chksum_tolerant( ) on 202205, test case is keep failure. Would you please have a check?
I see there was an discussion about the behavior in PR https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-mgmt/pull/7400, and the PR 7400 is closed without merge. What's the final conclusion of ip_packet_with_0xffff_chksum on mellanox ?

Currently seems the behavior on mellanox (SONiC os 202205) for 0xffff chksum is still drop.

all skips are currently added via tests_mark_conditions.yaml.  Adding within the script was done previously. Lately we have been adding all our skips via - https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-mgmt/blob/master/tests/common/plugins/conditional_mark/tests_mark_conditions.yaml
So @AnantKishorSharma  can you make the changes accordingly.
@neethajohn  and @kevinskwang , hope this is ok

@wangxin 
Yeah due to double commit of #7641. 

Resolved conflicts. Also checked that master's "gb:" section of the yaml is identical to this PRs "gb:" section to ensure no mishaps during conflict resolution or other oddities.

@kevinskwang @neethajohn 
Confirmed the 6 multi-flow tests passed on our 400G TB with this new code after the latest merge from PR #7436.
Marked ready for review.

@kevinskwang @neethajohn 
I've finished polishing up the code after that recent set of conflicts. The new port ID checker is interesting, but does not apply to this test since I've adapted it to use "indices", such that the IDs can be safely and automatically deduced across platforms. I renamed the qos.yml to avoid the new infra's regex from picking this up and thinking it's an ID it needs to correct.

I also removed the excess diff in other tests to keep it short. Those diffs are for the multi-flow test cases which are in the second upcoming PR.
